The Sheriff of Carroll County shall receive an annual salary as follows:
$71,532 beginning December 5, 2006;
$72,963 beginning December 4, 2007;
$74,422 beginning December 9, 2008; and
$75,910 beginning December 8, 2009, and thereafter.

The appointment of special deputy sheriffs under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph is subject to the following conditions:
The Sheriff may assign the duties of special deputies;
The Sheriff may terminate the appointment of a special deputy sheriff at will or on completion of the assignment for which the special deputy was appointed;
A special deputy sheriff shall remain an employee of the municipal corporation for the purpose of unemployment insurance or employee benefits; and
The Sheriff's liability insurance coverage within its terms shall be provided to a special deputy sheriff under this subsection only when the special deputy is acting within the special deputy's official duties.

The Sheriff of Cecil County shall receive an annual salary of:
$64,000 for calendar year 2007;
$66,500 for calendar year 2008;
$69,000 for calendar year 2009; and
$71,500 for calendar year 2010 and for each subsequent year.

The Sheriff shall appoint full-time or part-time employees, as provided in the county budget, to perform the duties of the Sheriff's department. These employees shall include:
Deputy sheriffs to perform law enforcement functions;
Deputy sheriffs to perform correctional functions;
Clerical and other civilian employees;
A director of the detention center; and
A community adult rehabilitation center administrator.

A full-time sworn law enforcement deputy sheriff at the rank of Sergeant and below may:
Take part in or refrain from taking part in forming, joining, supporting, or participating in a labor organization or its lawful activities;
Select a labor organization as the exclusive representative of the deputy sheriffs subject to this paragraph;
Engage in collective bargaining with the Sheriff and the County Commissioners of Cecil County, or the designee of the Sheriff and the County Commissioners, concerning wages, benefits, and any working conditions that are not included in subparagraph (v)4A of this paragraph through a labor organization certified as the exclusive representative of the deputy sheriffs subject to this paragraph;
Subject to item 2 of this subparagraph, enter into a collective bargaining agreement, through the exclusive representative of the deputy sheriffs subject to this paragraph, covering the wages, benefits, and other working conditions of the deputy sheriffs subject to this paragraph, to the extent that the agreement does not impair the rights of the Sheriff set forth in subparagraph (v)4 of this paragraph; and
Decertify a labor organization as the exclusive representative of the deputy sheriffs subject to this paragraph.

This paragraph does not apply to the following employees in the Charles County Sheriff's Office:
Sworn law enforcement officers or correctional officers in the Charles County Sheriff's Office at a rank of lieutenant or above;
Employees in appointed positions;
Civilian merit system employees;
Full-time reduced hours employees;
Part-time employees;
Contractual employees;
Temporary employees;
Emergency employees; or
Employees whose employment is administered under the county policies and procedures manual.

The Sheriff and the Office of the Sheriff for Charles County, through their appropriate officers and employees, may:
Determine the:
Maintain and improve the efficiency and effectiveness of governmental operations;
Determine the services to be rendered, operations to be performed, and technology to be used;
Determine the overall methods, processes, means, and classes of work or personnel by which governmental operations are to be conducted;
Hire, direct, supervise, and assign employees;
Set the qualifications of employees for appointment and promotions;
Set standards of conduct;
Adopt office rules, regulations, and procedures;
Provide a system of merit employment according to a standard of business efficiency; and
Take actions, not otherwise specified in this paragraph, to carry out the mission of the Office of the Sheriff of Charles County.

